  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Defrost the peas. Next, bring a large saucepan of salted water to the boil. Add the potatoes and boil for around 15 minutes, or until just cooked through. Take care not to overcook; they should be firm but just soft enough to poke your fork through without resistance."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While the potatoes are cooking, add the asparagus spears to the saucepan for 2 minutes, then remove them with tongs and place them in a colander. Rinse under cold running water to stop them cooking, then set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When the potatoes are done, drain them and set them aside in a colander to steam dry."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the whipped pea and artichoke purée, blend all the ingredients in a small food processor (which will give you a chunky texture) or a blender (for a smooth texture). Season to taste with plenty of salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the potatoes into bite-sized pieces. Cut the asparagus spears into 3cm pieces. Thinly slice the artichoke pieces."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Combine the potatoes, asparagus, artichokes, rocket and peas in a large bowl. Add the Dijon mustard, lemon juice and olive oil. Toss to combine, and season well to taste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To assemble, spoon plenty of the whipped pea mixture on to a plate. Top with the potatoes and vegetables, then drizzle with a little more olive oil, and sprinkle over the za’atar and sesame seeds, if using. Tear over the mint leaves and crumble on the vegan feta or tofu, then serve."
    }
  ],
